"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002597","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-12","<p>Local authorities submitted bids to deliver around 20,000 homes over the period 2019/20 to 2021/22 supported, in part, with around £800 million additional Affordable Homes Programme grant.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002597/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-12T17:15:48.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002597/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002597/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-11-06","Council Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 5 November 2018 to Question 186188 on Housing Revenue Account, how many units would have been built as a result of the £2.8 billion in additional borrowing requested by local authorities; and how much additional grant funding was requested by those authorities to finance those units.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","188715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002598","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-12","<p>The Government is committed to delivering the homes communities need. Through housing deals we are keen to support those places which come forward with a genuine ambition to build more homes.</p><p>We will continue to work with Milton Keynes Council and other local partners to help them realise their housing ambition. We are clear that any housing deal must meet the needs of all concerned.</p><p>My ministerial colleagues and I have regular discussions with MPs about local housing issues.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002598/answer",,,,,"188717 ; 188718","2018-11-12T17:15:19.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002598/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002598/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-11-06","Housing: Milton Keynes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what plans he has to make an announcement on the proposed Milton Keynes housing deal.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","188716"
