"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002647","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-11-19","<p>We are considering a number of options in the unlikely event that we reach March 2019 without a deal. The Home Office will set out further information in due course.</p><p>As the Immigration Minister has said, we do not intend to require visas from EU citizens in a no deal scenario and we welcome the commitment from the EU Commission that subject to reciprocity they will do the same for UK nationals entering the EU.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002647/answer",,,,,,"2018-11-19T10:04:50.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002647/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1002647/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-11-06","EU Nationals: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether children resident in the EU will be able to travel to the UK on identity cards in the event that the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","188690"
